Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you donâ€™t have symptoms.

There are currently no commercial options available to return to the UK from Sudan. The Sudanese authorities have suspended all international commercial passenger flights to and from Sudan.
The Sudanese authorities have closed all land borders (except for transfer of humanitarian aid).
The British Embassy is in contact with charter airlines, travel agents and other international organisations to identify opportunities for British people to return to the UK from Sudan. We will issue regular updates on this page and on Twitter and Facebook with the latest available information on departure options from Sudan. See Future Travel Options below.
We know this is concerning for British people trying to leave Sudan. You should:
Follow the advice of the Sudanese authorities, including local measures to help minimise your risk of exposure to coronavirus.
Keep in regular contact with family and friends at home, so they know you are safe and well.
Future travel options
If you are a British national in Sudan and wish to register your intention to return to the UK, please email the details listed below to our dedicated mailbox at stayincontactsudan@fco.gov.uk Please register your details with us even if you have previously been in contact so that we have the information listed below.
Your full name as shown on your passport
Passport number
Date of birth
Place of residence in UK
Where exactly you are currently staying in Sudan
Email address and telephone number (please ensure that you are able to receive phone calls from unidentified numbers, including internationally, in case we need to reach you)
Any specific medical needs/vulnerabilities
Evidence of your return journey to the UK, eg an itinerary or confirmed flight booking that you were unable to use or is imminent.
Copy of the details page of your passport
Please provide the information requested above for any family members with you in Sudan that are also seeking to return to the UK.
If you are registered with the British Embassy, we can alert you to any opportunities to book seats on flights departing Sudan for onward journeys to the UK. Such flights often come with a very tight deadline for submission of names of passengers. We will alert you, using your registration contact details, to any further departure options should these become available. This travel advice will also be updated when we are informed of other available options.
Help and Support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British Embassy on +249 156 77 55 00. The Embassy cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone. This page will be updated when departure options become available or, if you are registered with the Embassy, we will alert you. To get the latest information sign up for travel advice email alerts.
Arrival in the UK
When you arrive back in the UK, follow the guidance for when you return to the UK on steps you should take to protect yourself and others.
Further information
See more information and advice about staying where you are if you cannot return to the UK.
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
